post_text:
Information about Friday's football game at Glidden.
Glidden-Ralston Outdoor Venue Seating Restrictions:
1. All PK-8th grade students will need to sit with their family
2. We ask that all families practice social distancing both in the bleachers or the sidelines.
3. We will limit the amount of bleacher seating to encourage social distancing.
4. High School students will be asked to stay within their class and social distance if in the bleachers.
5. All attendees are highly encouraged to wear a mask.
6. Admission will be $5.00. We would ask that you have correct change if at all possible.
7. A concession stand will be available.
Please remember that these mitigations are always subject to change.
We would encourage you to stay home and watch the game if you do not have someone directly involved. The game will be livestreamed. Look for the link on our Facebook Page on Friday.

post_text:
Hello Hawkeye Families!

This is a reminder of our scheduled 1:30 early out tomorrow, September 2. We know, we know...we just finished a week of early outs! This was already scheduled on our board-approved calendar. Last week was a change made due to COVID. Thank you for all you are doing to support our students.

Calendar link: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RsQlTCoRRGqAhrG0JWor15jbUY7_C0Pj/view?usp=sharing

A couple other reminders:
*Please make sure your child is getting on the bus with a mask. We do have some extras, but they should be used only in emergency and not everyday. Also, remind them to wear the mask throughout the ride. Mrs. Ring will begin sending Bus Conduct Report Letters home this week.
*If your child is too young to be dropped off at their stop alone, please be at the location on time. We do have to stick to our route pickup/drop off times. We cannot leave students unattended and this creates a problem for our drivers.

post_text:
Harrison County Public Health administrator, Brad Brake, visited today for a Q and A with our 7th-12th grade students. Students had some in-depth and thoughtful questions. We feel like we understand the “why” just a bit more, which is so important for teens (and adults)!

All of us on campus, students included, are players on the West Harrison team!

Thank you, Mr. Brake, and HCPH for your support and important work! We appreciate the positive relationship we have built and know that if we do have to work together in the future, it will be a positive collaboration. 🖤🤍❤️

What a wonderful first day!

Students, thank you for being part of our team, working together to make our first day back such a success. You were awesome!

Parents and Guardians, thank you for preparing your child to be ready to face the challenges we have this year. They were all so wonderful and truly prepared to get back to work!!

Teachers and staff, THANK YOU for putting in the time to make our return to school such an outstanding success!

We are all a team, working together for our students and each other. Thank you, all!

I promise—more pictures tomorrow!

-Mrs. Ring

post_text:
Hawkeye families,

Our District Leadership Team is meeting weekly to make decisions about what our Return to Learn plan looks like when we return to school on August 24. We will update everyone via social media, text messaging, and email as soon as we can.

Our goal is to have students return to campus, but we also want to ensure our policy/procedures will mitigate exposure and is something we can sustain over time.

We are following guidance from the Department of Education and Harrison County Public Health. As we all know, change happens quickly and we have to respond accordingly and adjust our own planning as well.

Student learning and the safety of everyone on campus is of utmost importance and we want to be sure to make the best decisions for all.

We will be sending out our 2020-2021 calendar soon as well. :)

Thank you for your understanding and support!

Mr. Fonley and Mrs. Ring

We have GOOD news!

We just received word from the Governor and HCPH that we can continue with a graduation ceremony! It will look different, but will be ONE CEREMONY with EVERYONE!

More information will be sent out soon with more guidelines, but here is what we know:
1. It will be held June 21 at 6 PM. It will take place outside at the football field.
2. We will follow social distancing guidelines, similar to that of our ball games.
3. There will be a reception line, just no hugs or handshakes.
4. Seniors will choose a special person in their life to sit with during the ceremony. This person will present the graduate with their diploma.

Seniors:
* Mrs. Birdsall will send a survey to vote for attendants/ushers. VOTE!
* We need to practice! We will meet FRIDAY, June 19 at 8 - 9:30 am. Breakfast will be provided. Look for a Calendar invite and plan to be there.
* You will need to be in the Commons for robe fitting and preparation on June 21 at 5 pm

Please share this information with seniors and their families to ensure that everyone is informed!
~Mrs. Ring

post_text: West Harrison community members: Don’t forget that tonight is the “Light Up Iowa" event again and will take place from 8:00 to 8:30 p.m. to light up the football, baseball, and softball fields. The time represents the amount of days in which students have not been in school (1 minute for each day missed). The administration asks that you do not stop and get out of your car. You can stay in your car and drive through the West Harrison parking lot. This will continue every Friday through the end of May.

post_text: West Harrison community members- the "Light Up Iowa" event will take place from 8:00 to 8:25 p.m. at the football, baseball, and softball fields. The time represents the amount of days in which students have not been in school (1 minute for each day missed). After talking with the administration, it was decided that you may drive by or through the parking lot. Please do not stop and get out of your car. This will continue every Friday through the end of May. A YouTube video will be posted on the West Harrison website on Saturday.

post_text: Our small town is ever changing with the state of emergency our country is facing. Our local community is suffering in many ways but continues to support one another through various social distancing means. In an effort to show our schools and students that the State of Iowa recognizes their loss of activities, including sports, the Iowa High School Athletics Directors Association (IHSADA) is asking Iowa schools to participate in a “Light up Iowa” tribute. Each Friday night starting at 8, the football, baseball, and softball field lights will be seen from the sky as they are lit in honor of each day we have been out of school. We ask that community members keep social distancing practices and avoid gathering at the ball fields. If you follow social media posts and want to post your own image, please use the hashtag #lightupIA and include @ihsada.

Hello Hawkeye Family!

We are working to provide meals to our students in need of breakfast and lunch. We will be giving information out each week as to days of pick up and more so refer to our website, Facebook, and email as we move forward. See the attached flyer for more on this week's pickup/delivery days.

Form link: https://forms.gle/zkFyH8t3FLkvqbcr5
(it will also be emailed to all available addresses)

Thank you, all for your support!

post_text:
Juniors and families,

Tomorrow Tuesday, March 10th @ 6pm in the West Harrison High School library, ICAN will be giving a presentation about the FAFSA (free application for federal student aid). Steve Irvin will talk about the different ways to pay for college and about the importance of filling out the FAFSA to get financial aid. Hope to see everyone there!

- Mrs. Marshall

Toot toot! We just had the BEST transportation inspection ever! We received a 16/16; an A+.

Thank you, Dave Kuhlman for all of your hard work and preparation. Thank you, to our bus drivers as well!

We are lucky at West Harrison!
